reactor.rx.stream

Class RangeStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • reactor.rx.Stream<Long>
      • reactor.rx.stream.RangeStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.reactivestreams.Publisher<Long>, NonBlocking

    public final class RangeStream
extends Stream<Long>
    A Stream that emits N Long from the inclusive start value defined to the inclusive end and then complete.

    Since the stream retains the boundaries in a final field, any this#subscribe(org.reactivestreams.Subscriber) will replay all the range. This is a "Cold" stream.

    Create such stream with the provided factory, E.g.: 

     
 Streams.range(1, 10000).consume(
    log::info,
    log::error,
    (-> log.info("complete"))
 )
 
 
     
 Will log:
 1
 2
 3
 4
 complete
    Author:
    Stephane Maldini
